title: Arbab Lutfullah of PPPP wins PS-55 seat
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan Peoples Party Parliamentarians (PPPP) candidate Arbab Lutfullah has won the Sindh Assembly election from PS-55 Tharparkar-VI constituency by securing 107,552 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Arbab Zakaullah of Grand Democratic Alliance (GDA) who bagged 17,768 votes.
Overall votersâ€™ turn-out remained 65.81 per cent in the constituency.
